{{Infobox software | name = Bidji | logo = | screenshot = | caption = | developer = Bidji team | released = {{Start date and age|df=yes|2012|4}} | latest release version = 0.4.0 | latest release date = {{release date|2015|08|30}} | latest preview version = | latest preview date = | website = http://bidji.sourceforge.net/ | operating system = [[Cross-platform]] | programming language = [[Java (programming language)|Java]] | genre = [[Automatic programming|Code generation]] | license = [[GPL]] 3.0 }}
The '''Bidji''' project is a set of tools for data transformation and code generation.
The project is a mix between [[Apache Ant]] and the [[FreeMarker]] template engine. They combine together very well to offer maximum flexibility for code generation for any computer language (java, php, c++, etc.) or text documentation (docbook, markdown, plantuml, graphviz, etc.).
