{{Infobox scientist | name = Sabina Jeschke | image =Normen und Standards in Zeiten von 4.0 - Prof. Sabina Jeschke.jpg | alt = | caption = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1968|07|27|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Kungälv]], [[Sweden]] | death_date = <!--{{death date and age |YYYY|MM|DD|1968|07|27|df=y}} --> | death_place = | citizenship = [[Germany]] | nationality = [[Germany|German]] | alma_mater = [[Technical University of Berlin]] | website = <!--{{URL|www.example.com}}--> | footnotes = | imagesize = }}
'''Sabina Jeschke''' (born 27 July 1968 in [[Kungälv]], [[Sweden]]) is a German university professor for information sciences in mechanical engineering at the [[RWTH Aachen University]]. As of 10 November 2017, she was named member of the management board of [[Deutsche Bahn|Deutschen Bahn AG]] for digitalization and technology<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deutschebahn.com/en/group/ataglance/board_management/16126508/digitalisierung_technik_en.html|title=Member of the Management Board for Digitalization and Technology - Deutsche Bahn AG|website=www.deutschebahn.com}}</ref>. She is also the director of the Cybernetics Lab IMA/ZLW & IfU.<ref name="rwth-aachen.de">{{cite web|url=http://www.ima-zlw-ifu.rwth-aachen.de/|title=IMA,ZLW & IfU: Home|website=www.ima-zlw-ifu.rwth-aachen.de}}</ref> In the summer semester of 2017, she is on sabbatical leave to develop her research in the area of artificial consciousness (artificial / machine consciousness), and is involved in building a think tank "Strong Artificial Intelligence" at the Volvo Car Corporation in Göteborg. Since May 2015, Jeschke has been a member of the supervisory board of Körber AG, since April 2012 chairman of the board of VDI Aachen<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vdi.de/1663.0.html|title=VDI Verein Deutscher Ingenieure: Sprecher, Gestalter, Netzwerker|website=Verein Deutscher Ingenieure e.V.}}</ref>
==Life and work== Jeschke studied physics and computer sciences at the [[Technische Universität Berlin]], Germany.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ima-zlw-ifu.rwth-aachen.de/en/institute_cluster/staff/single_view/team/Sabina-Jeschke.html?no_cache=1|title=IMA,ZLW & IfU: Home|website=www.ima-zlw-ifu.rwth-aachen.de}}</ref> She completed her student research project during a research stay at the [[NASA Ames Research Center|NASA Ames Research Center Moffett Field]], California, USA under the direction of William (Bill) Borucki.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nasa-usa.de/centers/ames/news/releases/2004/borucki/borucki.html|title=NASA - William J. Borucki|website=www.nasa-usa.de}}</ref> During her doctoral studies she worked as a [[scientific researcher]] at the Institut für Mathematik at the [[Technische Universität Berlin]] and as an [[assistant professor]]/instructor at the [[Georgia Institute of Technology]] in Atlanta, US.
In 2004 she obtained her [[doctorate degree]] (Dr. rer. nat.) with [[honours degree|honors]]. After two years, Sabina Jeschke became a [[:de:Juniorprofessur|junior professor]] for New Media in Mathematics and Natural Sciences at the [[Technische Universität Berlin]]. As from 2007 she held a full professorship at the Institute for IT Service Technologies (IITS) and simultaneously became the director of the Central Information Technology Services (IT-Center) (RUS) at the [[University of Stuttgart]], Germany.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rus.uni-stuttgart.de/|title=Technische Informations- und Kommunikationsdienste (TIK) - Technische Informations- und Kommunikationsdienste - Universität Stuttgart|website=www.rus.uni-stuttgart.de}}</ref> Additionally she was a visiting professor and head of the former Center for Multimedia in Teaching and Research (MuLF) now innoCampus at the [[Technische Universität Berlin]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.innocampus.tu-berlin.de/|title=innoCampus: Home|website=www.innocampus.tu-berlin.de}}</ref> In 2009 she followed the call of the [[RWTH Aachen University]] and became a professor and the director of the Institute Cluster IMA/ZLW & IfU<ref name="rwth-aachen.de"/> at the Faculty of Mechanical Engineering.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.maschinenbau.rwth-aachen.de/|title=RWTH AACHEN UNIVERSITY Faculty of Mechanical Engineering - English|first=Faculty of Mechanical|last=Engineering|website=www.maschinenbau.rwth-aachen.de}}</ref> Until 2010 she additionally functioned as a visiting professor with scientific direction of research projects at the Institut für Technische Optik (ITO) of the [[University of Stuttgart]], Germany.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uni-stuttgart.de/ito/|title=Institut für Technische Optik - Institut für Technische Optik - Universität Stuttgart|website=www.uni-stuttgart.de}}</ref> From October 2011 to September 2016, she was vice dean of the Faculty of Mechanical Engineering at the [[RWTH Aachen University]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rwth-aachen.de/cms/main/root/Studium/Vor_dem_Studium/Schulprojekte/Veranstaltungen_fuer_Schuelerinnen_Schueler/KinderUni/Kinderuni_Roboter/~ccxz/Prof_Dr_Sabina_Jeschke/?lidx=1|title=*** Prof. Dr. Sabina Jeschke *** - RWTH AACHEN UNIVERSITY - English|first=RWTH Aachen|last=University|website=www.rwth-aachen.de}}</ref>
Some of the main areas of her research are [[robotics]] and [[automation]] technology (heterogeneous and cooperative robotics, web services in robotics), traffic and mobility (autonomous and semi-autonomous transport systems, international logistics, car2car & car2X models), [[Internet of things|Internet of Things]] and [[cyber-physical system]]s (industry 4.0, semantic web services), [[Artificial intelligence|Artificial Intelligence]] (data integration and data mining, multi-agency systems, cognitive computing), [[Human–computer interaction|human-machine interaction]] (virtual and remote laboratories, intelligent training environments), innovation research (innovation fields, trend monitoring) and information management (integration technologies for information services, innovative learning and teaching concepts).
She is a member and expert in numerous committees and commissions, inter alia Senior Member of the [[Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers]] (IEEE) since 2011 and a member of the Program Committee "Robotics and Automation" of the [[German Aerospace Center]] (DLR) since 2017. In July 2014, she was honored by the [https://en.gi.de/startpage.html German Society of Computer Science] (GI) with the recognition of Germany's digital minds.<ref name=":0">{{cite web|url=http://www.gi.de/aktuelles/meldungen/detailansicht/article/deutschlands-digitale-koepfe-ausgewaehlt.html|title=„Deutschlands digitale Köpfe“ ausgewählt|first=Gesellschaft für Informatik|last=(GI)|date=18 March 2018|website=www.gi.de}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ima-zlw-ifu.rwth-aachen.de/en/home/single_view/article/deutschlands_digitale_koepfe_ausgezeichnet.html|title=Germany's Digital Heads honored - IMA/ZWL & IfU|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170820040113/https://www.ima-zlw-ifu.rwth-aachen.de/en/home/single_view/article/deutschlands_digitale_koepfe_ausgezeichnet.html|archive-date=2017-08-20|dead-url=yes|access-date=}}</ref> For her contributions to a modern engineering education, she was awarded the Golden Nikola Tesla Chain of the International Society for Engineering Pedagogy (IGIP)<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.igip.org/|title=International Society for Engineering Pedagogy - IGIP|website=www.igip.org|language=en|access-date=2017-07-05}}</ref> in September 2015. Together with the [https://www.carologistics.org/ Carologistics] team of RWTH Aachen University and the University of Applied Sciences of Aachen she won the World Championship title in the [http://www.robocup-logistics.org/ RoboCup Logistics League] 2014, 2015 and 2016 for three years in a row.
